CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 29, 1961, pg. 24, reads: "Steeler Power for 1961 NFL Title Chase - Kidding "Boots" - One of the great relaxations at the Steelers' camp is taking time out to kid with Wallace (Boots) Lewis, club custodian-trainer. "Big Daddy" Lipscomb (left) and John Nisby, both All-Pro line choices, are enjoying themselves at the expense of "Boots."
TitMainTitle: Pittsburgh Steelers football players, no. 76 Gene "Big Daddy" Lipscomb, and no. 65 John Nisby, standing with arms on shoulders of club trainer Wallace "Boots" Lewis, posed on athletic field, Slippery Rock State Teachers College
